Afgri, Brait, Grand Parade, SacOil May Move: South African Stocks Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-03-02T06:45:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/afgri-ltd-grand-parade-sacoil-south-african-stock-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index snapped two
days of gains, losing 221.36, or 0.7 percent, to 32,050.73 at
the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.    Afgri Ltd . (AFR SJ): The handler of about a third of South
Africa’s grain said profit in the first half though December
retreated to 146 million rand ($21 million) from 156 million
rand a year earlier. Afgri rose 8 cents, or 1.1 percent, to 7.18
rand.    Brait SA  (BAT SJ): South Africa’s largest private equity
company said it will raise 6 billion rand and acquire stakes in
Pepkor Ltd., a clothing retailer, and Premier Foods.. The stock
declined 50 cents, or 2.2 percent, to 22 rand.    Grand Parade Investments Ltd . (GPL SJ): The  investment
company  with interests in tourism and gambling said earnings per
share will likely be between 30 percent and 50 percent higher in
the first half through December, compared with the same period a
year earlier. The company will publish its earnings results on
March 4. The stock declined 2 cents, or 0.7 percent, to 2.88
rand.    Hyprop Investments Ltd . (HYP SJ): The property investment
company said its total distribution per combined unit rose 8.8
percent to 3.57 rand in the year through December. The stock
increased 34 cents, or 0.6 percent, to 54.54 rand.    Petmin Ltd . (PET): The country’s largest anthracite coal
miner said profit for the first half through December advanced
to 47.3 million rand from 46.6 million rand a year earlier. The
stock added 3 cents, or 1 percent, to 3.12 rand.  SacOil Holdings Ltd. (SCL SJ): The oil and natural gas
explorer, which said yesterday it bought into a hydrocarbon
field in  Nigeria , cancelled a media briefing about its plan to
trade shares on the London Stock Exchange. SacOil increased 8
cents, or 4.1 percent, to 2.04 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) declined 1.4 percent to
$26.65. AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) added 0.4 percent to
$49.05. BHP Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) fell 1.2 percent to $78.36.
DRDGold Ltd. (DROOY US) gained 2.7 percent to $4.90. Gold Fields
Ltd. (GFI US) slumped 0.2 percent to $17.88. Harmony Gold Mining
Co. (HMY US) lost 0.3 percent to $11.75. Impala Platinum
Holdings (IMPUY US) weakened 3.3 percent to $28.47. Sappi Ltd.
(SPP US) declined 3.7 percent to $5.15. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) fell
3.3 percent to $53.06.  To contact the reporter on this story:
